Github actions has three core components namely,

1. Workflow 

 -  An automated process capable of doing one or more Jobs
 -  Each workflow can have an optional name and keyword

2. Jobs

 -  Jobs are building blocks of a workflow there can be one or more jobs inside a workflow
 -  Each job is associated with a runner (github hosted or self hosted)


3. Steps

 -  Steps in github actions are individual tasks that makeup a job

Actions

    Actions within github workflows are pre-built, reusable automation components designed for a specific tasks.
    Actions also facilitate integration with third-party tools and services, therefore enhancing your project's automation and capabilities.